ue to his leadership of #OperationDudula, which has been responsible for attacks on foreign nationals in various parts of the country. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1232276" src="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/finalCABCfacesoflux-inset-8.png" alt="" width="720" height="547" srcset="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/finalCABCfacesoflux-inset-8.png 1120w, https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/finalCABCfacesoflux-inset-8.png?resize=480,365 480w, https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/finalCABCfacesoflux-inset-8.png?resize=768,584 768w, https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/finalCABCfacesoflux-inset-8.png?resize=720,547 720w, https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/finalCABCfacesoflux-inset-8.png?resize=350,266 350w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" />Last month, the CABC reported that the first mentions of #OperationDudula were recorded around June 2021, when posters of #OperationDudula’s plan to remove foreign nationals from Soweto began circulating, with the first spike recorded around Youth Day. An advanced Twitter search reveals that the @nhlanhla_lux_ account made no mentions of the hashtag between June 2014 (when the account was created) and December 2021. The graph below indicates the account first used the #OperationDudula around 30 January this year. <img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1232380" src="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Screenshot-2022-04-10-at-18.22.19.png" alt="" width="720" height="243" srcset="https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Screenshot-2022-04-10-at-18.22.19.png 904w, https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Screenshot-2022-04-10-at-18.22.19.png?resize=480,162 480w, https://www.dailymaverick.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Screenshot-2022-04-10-at-18.22.19.png?resize=768,259 768w, https